Rafael Gorski's personal vimfiles.

I use vim with junction of Visual Studio's VSVim in a Windows Machine.
I also use OSX however not as dev tool.

Installation instructions (Linux):
- git clone https://github.com/RafaelGorski/vimfiles ~/.vim
- echo "source ~/.vim/.vimrc" > ~/.vimrc
- cd ~/.vim
- git submodule update --init

Installation instructions (Windows, no Powershell):
- git clone https://github.com/RafaelGorski/vimfiles ~/vimfiles
- echo "source $($($env:HOME).Replace('\', '/'))/vimfiles/.vimrc" > ~/_vimrc
- cd ~/.vim
- git submodule update --init

Pre-requisites
http://www.vim.org/download.php


Other Vim supports:
https://visualstudiogallery.msdn.microsoft.com/59ca71b3-a4a3-46ca-8fe1-0e90e3f79329


